Description: Up for auction is a cream color Guild model S-60 in a hard shell case. In good to very good condition with some normal paint fading and small chips in the paint here and there. No damage or cracks or repairs to the guitar. The case is a plastic hard shell unbranded case with a small notch cut in the inside to fit the guitar perfectly. The case has some scratches on it(see pictures) but no damage or cracks. This guitar is almost all original except for the gold Sperzel locking tuners that are made in the USA. The paint is original but some had put stickers on it and the white part of the paint was the original color and the rest turned a darker yellow over the years. There is some chipping by the bridge. The guitar sounds very good(like it has a PAF pickup) and has low string action. The serial number is #177212 dating this to 1978. The volume knob and tone knob are a little tight to turn but not too bad. There is a little scratchy noise when turning the pots and they should be sprayed with electronic contact cleaner due to this being normal on vintage guitars. Below are the specs.
